Taking into account that we already have almost the first basic ecosystem services ‚Äì the crypto exchange and the payment system, we expect the planned development of our project and the increase in the number of users. First of all, there will be a demand on tokens to pay for ecosystem services. Secondly, the number of tokens will decrease due to their redemption and destruction. Using Portfolio and RAMM strategies, the investor can withdraw his investments at any time without having to seek the trader‚Äôs agreement. In the option of SAMM, withdrawals are possible only on demand from the investor at intervals set in advance. This allows the trader to implement broader strategies, and to be confident of having sufficient resources available. By means of this and the availability of leverage, the expected return with the SAMM is the highest.

Author: nixon99
Title: It's an old ANN thread. Please, follow the link shown below to the new thread
Body: Thank you for your interest in our ecosystem activities! Concerning trading bots - we have a lot of experience working with them on the forex market. It‚Äôs impossible to answer for sure "yes" or "no" - first, you need to decide how you want to use these bots. A trading bot is a tool that needs to be properly configured and used correctly. Its behavior is limited by the instructions. In conditions of constantly changing crypto market, bots can be very effective on a strictly defined type of transactions, and are ineffective in other conditions. Bots can‚Äôt analyze news, FOMO, FUD, and other irrational factors of crypto market. These are their main disadvantage at present.

Title: It's an old ANN thread. Please, follow the link shown below to the new thread
Body: Good question! In fact, the Azbit ecosystem offers many options for solving this issue. From the very beginning an investor needs to define, what level of investment risk is admissible for him. Cryptocurrency trading is a highly profitable industry, but is also a high-risk industry. Let's just say you prefer a minimum risk, so you can use the service of margin lending within the Azbit ecosystem ‚Äì lend money to traders at low interest rate. In this case, the trader's own assets will act as a guarantee of the repayment. The risks are minimal, but the profit (in comparison with SAMM-RAMM-Portfolio) is modest.

But with the SAMM option, a trader can earn more by using leverage, and investors will receive more profit.

Body: O–∫) In relating the details - the bank will provide a number of unique services, which are not directly related to payment systems. For example, resale of liquidity, deposit storage of fiat and cryptocurrency on cold wallets. The bank‚Äôs basic role is to support all the Azbit ecosystem services and thereby reduce internal operating expenses and increase profit. Bank‚Äôs services: -Payments and accounts in a variety of national currencies -Crypto-fiat exchange, and vice versa. -Deposit accounts -Segregated accounts -Brokerage -Payment cards -Credit cards (in case of obtaining Visa/Mastercard Principal Member status)  Our payment system will provide support and processing for all online and cryptocurrency payments. At the same time, the bank will carry out interbank transfers in the fiat currencies. That is, the functions of the payment system will include:  -Online exchange between users -Online payments -Built-in currency conversion -Instant Exchange -Fiat currency exchange -P2P debt platform -Cryptocurrency portfolio-backed P2P lending

Author: nixon99
Title: It's an old ANN thread. Please, follow the link shown below to the new thread
Body: Liquidity describes the degree to which an asset or security can be quickly bought or sold in the market without affecting the asset's price. That is, if there are enough participants and funds on the crypto market or crypto exchange, you can buy or sell the necessary coins at the average market price - and do it quickly. If there is not enough liquidity - you will either be forced to exhibit/accept unprofitable prices to find a buyer/seller more quickly. Or you will wait very long for the buyer/seller. Liquidity on big and popular exchanges is higher, on small and little known - lower.
